PNMP came after Yarn Plug'n'Play.
It also supports Plug'n'Play, but it can also solve the phantom dependencies issue without messing with node.

It does this by hiding the dependencies node shouldn't resolve in node_modules/.pnpm.

Run these like this:

```
corepack pnpm install

# works
corepack pnpm node 1-use-direct-dependency.js

# fails
node 2-use-indirect-dependency.js
node 3-use-distant-node-module.js
```
